	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Mon</date></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>June 1&#44; 1857</date></p>
				<p><hi rend="underline"><add>Hebrew</add></hi></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Buffalo</placeName>&#44; <date>8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sivan&#44; 1857</date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#40;<date>June</date>&#41;</p>
				<p>To my dearest friend&#44; Sweet&#45;singer of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44;<lb/> etc. etc.</p>
				<p>Dear friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I <del>am not</del> have no intention to burden<lb/> you with words&#44; but only to reveal to you<lb/> what I saw yesterday when I was at the<lb/> Synagogue.  Half the books that used to be<lb/> there are stolen&#44; and there are left for you<lb/> only a very small number.  Only the Bible<lb/> is still to be found.  The rest are gone forever.<lb/>  The Hazan&#44; who lives there&#44; told me that he<lb/> has found only these.  He had come to <placeName>Buffalo</placeName><lb/> after <date>Passover</date>&#44; and does not know who took<lb/> the rest of the books.  Therefore&#44; I want to<lb/> ask you what to do if any people should<lb/> want to purchase the rest cheap.  Shall I<lb/> sell or not.  There is no further news.  I<lb/> expect a clear answer soon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Yitshok Itzik</persName> son of <persName>Moses Slatky</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">The Address</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Isaac M. Slattkey</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Box 2648</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Buffalo N. Y.</placeName></p>
		</body>
